[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Python companion is well-structured and faithfully implements the pseudocode from the main recipe. The pipeline flows logically from PubMed ingestion through NER, relation extraction, normalization, evidence grading, conflict detection, and Neptune graph insertion. The code is pedagogically sound, building understanding progressively. boto3 API calls are correct, S3 keys have no leading slashes, and the Gremlin queries use appropriate Neptune patterns. I found one issue with the entity marker insertion logic in the relation extraction step that would produce incorrect results, and a few warnings about patterns that could mislead learners.
